text: Bolshesidorovskoye () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Bolshesidorovskoye Rural Settlement of Krasnogvardeysky District, Adygea, Russia. The population was 1538 as of 2018. There are 14 streets. == Geography == The village is located 22 km south-east from Krasnogvardeyskoye, on the Psenapha River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Krasnogvardeysky District
title: Bolshesidorovskoye
